WEBVTT

00:19.100 --> 00:20.140
CHAPTER XVII.

00:20.600 --> 00:24.780
The being finished speaking and fixed his looks upon me in the expectation of a reply.

00:25.600 --> 00:32.760
But I was bewildered, perplexed, and unable to arrange my ideas sufficiently to understand the full extent of his proposition.

00:35.360 --> 00:43.200
You must create a female for me, with whom I can live in the interchange of those sympathies necessary for my being.

00:44.200 --> 00:51.880
This you alone can do, and I demanded of you as a right which you must not refuse to concede.

00:52.600 --> 01:00.180
The latter part of his tale had kindled anew in me the anger that had died away while he narrated his peaceful life among the cottagers.

01:01.260 --> 01:06.080
And as he said this, I could no longer suppress the rage that burned within me.

01:06.540 --> 01:12.000
I do refuse it, I replied, and no torture shall ever extort a consent from me.

01:12.520 --> 01:18.560
You may render me the most miserable of men, but you shall never make me base in my own eyes.

01:18.560 --> 01:25.220
Shall I create another like yourself whose joint wickedness might desolate the world? Be gone.

01:25.940 --> 01:30.540
I have answered you. You may torture me, but I will never consent.

01:31.680 --> 01:34.340
You are in the wrong, replied the fiend.

01:35.440 --> 01:39.480
And instead of threatening, I am content to reason with you.

01:40.120 --> 01:47.620
I am malicious because I am miserable. Am I not shunned and hated by all mankind?

01:48.560 --> 01:52.000
You, my creator, would tear me to pieces and triumph.

01:53.200 --> 01:58.520
Remember that, and tell me why I should pity man more than he pities me.

01:59.440 --> 02:07.020
You would not call it murder if you could precipitate me into one of those ice rifts and destroy my frame, the work of your own hands.

02:07.900 --> 02:10.960
Shall I respect man when he condemns me?

02:10.960 --> 02:21.660
Let him live with me in the interchange of kindness, and instead of injury I would bestow every benefit upon him with tears of gratitude at his acceptance.

02:22.980 --> 02:29.800
But that cannot be. The human senses are insurmountable barriers to our union.

02:31.060 --> 02:34.780
Yet mine shall not be the submission of abject slavery.

02:34.780 --> 02:45.080
I will revenge my injuries. If I cannot inspire love, I will cause fear, and chiefly towards you, my archenemy.

02:45.580 --> 02:50.700
Because, my creator, do I swear inextinguishable hatred.

02:51.600 --> 03:02.040
Have a care. I will work at your destruction, nor finish until I desolate your heart, so that you shall curse the hour of your birth.

03:02.040 --> 03:10.120
A fiendish rage animated him as he said this. His face was wrinkled into contortions too horrible for human eyes to behold.

03:11.160 --> 03:13.160
Presently he calmed himself and proceeded.

03:14.460 --> 03:22.700
I intend to reason. This passion is detrimental to me, for you do not reflect that you are the cause of its success.

03:23.920 --> 03:30.540
If any being felt emotions of benevolence towards me, I should return them a hundred and a hundredfold.

03:31.400 --> 03:37.040
But for that one creature's sake, I would make peace with the whole kind.

03:38.320 --> 03:42.140
But I now indulge in dreams of bliss that cannot be realized.

03:43.100 --> 03:46.620
What I ask of you is reasonable and moderate.

03:47.360 --> 03:52.760
I demand a creature of another sex, but as hideous as myself.

03:52.760 --> 04:00.480
The gratification is small, but it is all that I can receive, and it shall content me.

04:01.080 --> 04:06.960
It is true. We shall be monsters, cut off from all the world.

04:07.660 --> 04:11.240
But on that account, we shall be more attached to one another.

04:12.020 --> 04:19.300
Our lives will not be happy, but they will be harmless, and free from the misery I now feel.

04:20.100 --> 04:28.500
Oh, my creator, make me happy. Let me feel gratitude towards you for one benefit.

04:29.300 --> 04:33.560
Let me see that I excite the sympathy of some existing thing.

04:34.760 --> 04:37.320
Do not deny me my requests.

04:38.540 --> 04:43.860
I was moved. I shuddered when I thought of the possible consequences of my consent.

04:45.080 --> 04:48.020
But I felt that there was some justice in his argument.

04:48.900 --> 04:54.140
His tale and the feelings he now expressed proved him to be a creature of fine sensations.

04:55.960 --> 05:01.760
And did I not, as his maker, owe him all the portion of happiness that it was in my power to bestow?

05:02.480 --> 05:05.800
He saw my change of feelings and continued.

05:07.080 --> 05:13.580
If you consent, neither you nor any other human being shall ever see us again.

05:14.120 --> 05:17.480
I will go to the vast wilds of South America.

05:18.020 --> 05:24.520
My food is not that of man. I do not destroy the lamb and the kid to glut my appetite.

05:25.360 --> 05:28.120
Acorns and berries afford me sufficient nourishment.

05:28.980 --> 05:33.360
My companion will be of the same nature as myself, and will be content with the same fare.

05:34.400 --> 05:36.840
We shall make a bed of dried leaves.

05:37.580 --> 05:42.300
The sun will shine on us as on man, and will ripen our food.

05:43.060 --> 05:47.480
The picture I present to you is peaceful and human,

05:48.460 --> 05:53.120
and you must feel that you could deny it only in the wantonness of power and cruelty.

05:54.180 --> 05:59.340
Pityless as you have been towards me, I now see compassion in your eyes.

05:59.980 --> 06:05.780
Let me seize the favorable moment and persuade you to promise what I so ardently desire.

06:06.860 --> 06:11.860
You propose, replied I, to fly from the habitations of man,

06:12.740 --> 06:16.600
to dwell in those wilds where the beasts of the field will be your only companions.

06:17.800 --> 06:24.180
How can you, who long for the love and sympathy of man, persevere in this exile?

06:24.780 --> 06:30.180
You will return and again seek their kindness, and you will meet with their detestation.

06:30.180 --> 06:36.320
Your evil passions will be renewed, and you will then have a companion to aid you in the task of destruction.

06:37.260 --> 06:41.000
This may not be. Cease to argue the point, for I cannot consent.

06:43.140 --> 06:45.560
How inconstant are your feelings!

06:46.720 --> 06:50.220
But a moment ago you were moved by my representations.

06:52.100 --> 06:55.020
And why do you again harden yourself to my complaints?

06:55.020 --> 07:00.440
I swear to you, by the earth which I inhabit and by you that made me,

07:00.840 --> 07:05.680
that with the companion you bestow I will quit the neighborhood of man and dwell,

07:05.920 --> 07:09.360
as it may chance, in the most savage of places.

07:10.340 --> 07:14.540
My evil passions will have fled, for I shall meet with sympathy.

07:15.560 --> 07:22.040
My life will flow quietly away, and in my dying moments I shall not curse my Maker.

07:23.040 --> 07:25.360
His words had a strange effect upon me.

07:26.560 --> 07:30.700
I compassionated him, and sometimes felt a wish to console him.

07:31.880 --> 07:38.000
But when I looked upon him, when I saw the filthy mass that moved and talked,

07:39.220 --> 07:44.740
my heart sickened, and my feelings were altered to those of horror and hatred,

07:45.960 --> 07:48.120
I tried to stifle these sensations.

07:48.120 --> 07:51.500
I thought that as I could not sympathize with him,

07:51.780 --> 07:55.520
I had no right to withhold from him the small portion of happiness

07:55.520 --> 07:58.040
which was yet in my power to bestow.

07:59.240 --> 08:03.240
You swear, I said, to be harmless,

08:04.160 --> 08:10.280
but have you not already shown a degree of malice that should reasonably make me distrust you?

08:10.280 --> 08:15.520
May not even this be a feint that will increase your triumph

08:15.520 --> 08:17.940
by affording a wider scope for your revenge?

08:19.900 --> 08:26.060
How is this I must not be trifled with, and I demand an answer.

08:27.140 --> 08:31.200
If I have no ties and no affections, hatred and vice must be my portion.

08:32.000 --> 08:35.860
The love of another will destroy the cause of my crimes,

08:35.860 --> 08:40.940
and I shall become a thing of whose existence everyone will be ignorant.

08:42.260 --> 08:46.600
My vices are the children of a forced solitude that I abhor,

08:47.420 --> 08:53.820
and my virtues will necessarily arise when I live in communion with an equal.

08:54.740 --> 08:58.380
I shall feel the affections of a sensitive being

08:58.380 --> 09:02.860
and become linked to the chain of existence and events from which I am now excluded.

09:03.420 --> 09:06.680
I paused some time to reflect on all he had related

09:06.680 --> 09:09.360
and the various arguments which he had employed.

09:10.560 --> 09:14.920
I thought of the promise of virtues which he had displayed on the opening of his existence

09:14.920 --> 09:19.240
and the subsequent blight of all kindly feeling by the loathing and scorn

09:19.240 --> 09:21.720
which his protectors had manifested towards him.

09:22.960 --> 09:27.000
His power and threats were not omitted in my calculations.

09:27.620 --> 09:30.460
A creature who could exist in the ice caves of the glaciers

09:30.460 --> 09:34.840
and hide himself from pursuit among the ridges of inaccessible precipices

09:34.840 --> 09:38.860
was a being possessing faculties it would be vain to cope with.

09:39.740 --> 09:41.480
After a long pause of reflection,

09:42.260 --> 09:45.900
I concluded that the justice due both to him and my fellow creatures

09:45.900 --> 09:49.200
demanded of me that I should comply with his request.

09:50.280 --> 09:52.340
Turning to him, therefore, I said,

09:53.560 --> 09:57.720
I consent to your demand, on your solemn oath to quit Europe forever,

09:57.720 --> 10:00.420
and every other place in the neighborhood of man,

10:00.940 --> 10:05.240
as soon as I shall deliver into your hands a female who will accompany you in your exile.

10:06.140 --> 10:11.980
I swear, he cried, by the sun and by the blue sky of heaven

10:11.980 --> 10:15.040
and by the fire of love that burns my heart,

10:15.820 --> 10:22.200
that if you grant my prayer, while they exist, you shall never behold me again.

10:23.460 --> 10:25.900
Depart to your home and commence your labors.

10:25.900 --> 10:30.300
I shall watch their progress with unutterable anxiety,

10:31.500 --> 10:36.060
and fear not, but that when you are ready, I shall appear.

10:37.220 --> 10:38.900
Seeing this, he suddenly quitted me,

10:39.760 --> 10:41.740
fearful perhaps of any change in my sentiments.

10:42.640 --> 10:45.960
I saw him descend the mountain with greater speed than the flight of an eagle,

10:46.920 --> 10:50.640
and quickly lost among the undulations of the sea of ice.

10:52.160 --> 10:54.000
His tail had occupied the whole day,

10:54.000 --> 10:57.180
and the sun was on the verge of the horizon when he departed.

10:58.220 --> 11:01.280
I knew that I ought to hasten my descent towards the valley,

11:01.980 --> 11:04.100
as I should soon be encompassed in darkness.

11:05.180 --> 11:07.400
But my heart was heavy and my steps slow.

11:08.140 --> 11:10.760
The labor of winding among the little paths of the mountain,

11:11.440 --> 11:14.220
and fixing my feet firmly as I advanced, perplexed me,

11:15.140 --> 11:19.920
occupied as I was by the emotions which the occurrences of the day had produced.

11:20.860 --> 11:24.600
Night was far advanced when I came to the halfway resting place,

11:24.860 --> 11:26.660
and seated myself beside the fountain.

11:27.800 --> 11:31.720
The stars shone at intervals as the clouds passed from over them.

11:32.560 --> 11:35.100
The dark pines rose before me,

11:36.200 --> 11:39.080
and every here and there a broken tree lay on the ground.

11:40.000 --> 11:41.840
It was a scene of wonderful solemnity,

11:42.740 --> 11:44.980
and stirred strange thoughts within me.

11:45.880 --> 11:47.280
I wept bitterly,

11:48.200 --> 11:50.600
and clasping my hands in agony I exclaimed,

11:51.460 --> 11:53.980
Oh, stars and clouds and winds,

11:55.060 --> 11:57.400
you're all about to mock me.

11:57.640 --> 11:59.220
If you really pity me,

11:59.600 --> 12:03.560
crush sensation and memory that may become as nought.

12:04.080 --> 12:09.480
But if nought, depart, depart, and leave me in darkness.

12:10.760 --> 12:12.700
These were wild and miserable thoughts,

12:12.700 --> 12:17.240
but I cannot describe to you how the eternal twinkling of the stars weighed upon me,

12:17.300 --> 12:24.180
and how I listened to every blast of wind as if it were a dull, ugly siroc on its way to consume me.

12:24.900 --> 12:28.240
Morning dawned before I arrived at the village of Chamouni.

12:28.800 --> 12:31.340
I took no rest, but returned immediately to Geneva.

12:32.440 --> 12:35.800
Even in my own heart I could give no expression to my sensations.

12:36.800 --> 12:38.760
They weighed on me with a mountain's weight,

12:39.200 --> 12:42.100
and their excess destroyed my agony beneath them.

12:43.060 --> 12:47.440
Thus I returned home, and entering the house presented myself to the family.

12:48.720 --> 12:51.280
My haggard and wild appearance awoke intense alarm,

12:52.140 --> 12:53.500
but I answered no question.

12:53.940 --> 12:55.020
Scarcely did I speak.

12:55.740 --> 12:58.080
I felt as if I were placed under a ban,

12:58.620 --> 13:00.940
as if I had no right to claim their sympathies,

13:01.580 --> 13:05.840
as if never more might I enjoy companionship with them.

13:06.760 --> 13:09.780
Yet even thus I loved them to adoration,

13:09.780 --> 13:17.400
and, to save them, I resolved to dedicate myself to my most abhorred task.

13:18.440 --> 13:24.080
The prospect of such an occupation made every other circumstance of existence pass before me like a dream,

13:24.700 --> 13:28.920
and that thought only had to be the reality of life.

